= Benita Galeana

*Corriente: los ortodoxos. Cada consejo suyo fortalece a su corriente — y las otras participan menos.*

She sold gum on the street as a girl in Guerrero, taught herself to read as a grown woman, and was jailed fifty-eight times for the crime of standing on corners saying true things loudly. Her autobiography is taught in universities she was never allowed to enter. She is past sixty now and the granaderos still handle her carefully, not out of chivalry but because they have learned what it costs on the front pages when they don't.

