She tells the students about selling gum, about the fifty-eight arrests, about hiding Cuban sailors in her kitchen, and she gets the only thing harder to get than applause: silence, the kind where nobody wants to be the first to breathe. The generation that thinks history began in 1968 discovers, for one evening, its grandmothers.

@benita_base
title: La fe de la base
subtitle: The rank and file's faith is a resource too. Tend the people who show up when no one is watching.
